<p>

First off, Jeff and I love <a href = http://www.reddwarf.co.uk/>RedDwarf.</a>

<p>

Secondly, every shop has a naming convention.

<p>

At home I have astronomical naming: Saturn, Venus, Crater, Hubble, Haley, Meteor, Mars...  <br>
Jeff has electical (he used to work at Fluke): LED, Capacitor, Diode...  

<p>

It's up to the admin(s) to pick a convention.  Sometimes it's something really boring like Server01, SVR01-13, boring1, boring2.  Since we both like the Red Dwarf series we went with that.

<p>

On to the boxen.

