  Jupiter Mining Corp is the company that hired the cast of the Red Dwarf series.  It's also a big planet.  Jupiter the computer however is the main filserver and is also very bi.  Started originally with 200Gb of disk space, now is 2Tb!  Dual Xeon 3GHz processors (4 virtual CPUs).  Hefty.
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td align = center>
  <img src = io.jpg>
</td>
<td>
<font size = 2 face = "Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">
  What happens if Jupiter goes down due to hardware failure?  We have a mirror box called Io.  Io is almost exactly the same hardware as Jupiter so in a pinch it can act as Jupiter.  Everytime you save/delete/rename/do anything to a file on Jupiter, it alos happens on Io.  While not astronomically accurate (Io is a moon of Jupiter and quite different physically), it's also a play on words as in computer land I/O is Input/Output.
</td>
</tr>

